WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:22.320 align:middle line:90%


00:00:22.320 --> 00:00:25.792 align:middle line:84%
[MUSIC - LEE COURINGTON, "THE
 BEGINNING"]

00:00:25.792 --> 00:00:51.088 align:middle line:90%


00:00:51.088 --> 00:00:54.700 align:middle line:84%
>> The world's greatest
spiritual teachers from ancient

00:00:54.700 --> 00:00:59.020 align:middle line:84%
to modern times have shared
the view that the deepest truth

00:00:59.020 --> 00:01:03.250 align:middle line:84%
of our being is not the property
of one particular religion

00:01:03.250 --> 00:01:07.370 align:middle line:84%
or spiritual tradition but
can be found within the heart

00:01:07.370 --> 00:01:08.170 align:middle line:90%
of each person.

00:01:08.170 --> 00:01:20.565 align:middle line:90%


00:01:20.565 --> 00:01:24.820 align:middle line:84%
The poet Rumi said,
"Where is that moon

00:01:24.820 --> 00:01:28.170 align:middle line:90%
that never rises or sets?

00:01:28.170 --> 00:01:34.050 align:middle line:84%
Where is that soul that is
neither with nor without us?

00:01:34.050 --> 00:01:37.600 align:middle line:90%
Don't say it is here or there.

00:01:37.600 --> 00:01:42.810 align:middle line:84%
All creation is 'That' but
for the eyes that can see."

00:01:42.810 --> 00:02:41.692 align:middle line:90%


00:02:41.692 --> 00:02:45.185 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:45.185 --> 00:02:50.230 align:middle line:90%


00:02:50.230 --> 00:02:53.000 align:middle line:84%
In the story of
the Tower of Babel,

00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:57.690 align:middle line:84%
humanity fragmented into
countless languages, beliefs,

00:02:57.690 --> 00:03:00.980 align:middle line:90%
cultures, and interests.

00:03:00.980 --> 00:03:05.160 align:middle line:84%
Babel means literally
"the gate of God."

00:03:05.160 --> 00:03:09.960 align:middle line:84%
The gate is our thinking mind,
our conditioned structures.

00:03:09.960 --> 00:03:14.810 align:middle line:90%


00:03:14.810 --> 00:03:19.130 align:middle line:84%
For those who come to
realize their true nature,

00:03:19.130 --> 00:03:21.980 align:middle line:84%
their essence beyond
name and form,

00:03:21.980 --> 00:03:24.860 align:middle line:84%
they are initiated
into the great mystery

00:03:24.860 --> 00:03:26.510 align:middle line:90%
of what lies beyond the gate.

00:03:26.510 --> 00:03:37.130 align:middle line:90%


00:03:37.130 --> 00:03:40.670 align:middle line:10%
An ancient parable,
the elephant parable,

00:03:40.670 --> 00:03:44.750 align:middle line:10%
has been used to describe how
various traditions are actually

00:03:44.750 --> 00:03:46.820 align:middle line:10%
all pointing to one great truth.

00:03:46.820 --> 00:03:49.470 align:middle line:90%


00:03:49.470 --> 00:03:53.040 align:middle line:84%
A group of blind people are
each touching a different part

00:03:53.040 --> 00:03:56.220 align:middle line:84%
of an elephant, getting
a certain impression

00:03:56.220 --> 00:04:00.270 align:middle line:90%
of what an elephant is.

00:04:00.270 --> 00:04:03.210 align:middle line:84%
But the person standing
at the elephant's leg

00:04:03.210 --> 00:04:05.920 align:middle line:84%
describes the elephant
as being like a tree.

00:04:05.920 --> 00:04:07.746 align:middle line:84%
[MUSIC - DANIEL SCHMIDT
AND VICKI HANSEN,

00:04:07.746 --> 00:04:08.620 align:middle line:90%
"THE GAYATRI MANTRA"]

00:04:08.620 --> 00:04:14.080 align:middle line:84%
The person at the tail says
the elephant is like a rope.

00:04:14.080 --> 00:04:16.480 align:middle line:84%
The elephant is
like a spear, says

00:04:16.480 --> 00:04:20.089 align:middle line:90%
the one standing at the tusk.

00:04:20.089 --> 00:04:23.840 align:middle line:84%
If one touches the ear, it seems
the elephant is like a fan.

00:04:23.840 --> 00:04:26.410 align:middle line:90%


00:04:26.410 --> 00:04:29.200 align:middle line:84%
The person touching
the side is adamant

00:04:29.200 --> 00:04:30.970 align:middle line:84%
that the elephant
is like a wall.

00:04:30.970 --> 00:04:34.240 align:middle line:90%


00:04:34.240 --> 00:04:38.200 align:middle line:84%
The problem is we touch
our piece of the elephant,

00:04:38.200 --> 00:04:41.020 align:middle line:84%
and we believe our
experience is the only truth.

00:04:41.020 --> 00:04:43.860 align:middle line:90%


00:04:43.860 --> 00:04:46.470 align:middle line:84%
We don't acknowledge
or appreciate

00:04:46.470 --> 00:04:50.460 align:middle line:84%
that each person's experience
is a different facet

00:04:50.460 --> 00:04:51.960 align:middle line:90%
of the same animal.

00:04:51.960 --> 00:04:55.411 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING SANSKRIT]

00:04:55.411 --> 00:05:04.285 align:middle line:90%


00:05:04.285 --> 00:05:08.229 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:05:08.229 --> 00:05:17.600 align:middle line:90%


00:05:17.600 --> 00:05:20.840 align:middle line:84%
The perennial philosophy
is an understanding

00:05:20.840 --> 00:05:24.170 align:middle line:84%
that all spiritual and
religious traditions

00:05:24.170 --> 00:05:29.920 align:middle line:84%
share a single universal truth,
a mystical or transcendent

00:05:29.920 --> 00:05:34.540 align:middle line:84%
reality upon which foundation
all spiritual knowledge

00:05:34.540 --> 00:05:36.030 align:middle line:90%
and doctrine has grown.

00:05:36.030 --> 00:05:46.410 align:middle line:90%


00:05:46.410 --> 00:05:50.340 align:middle line:84%
Swami Vivekananda summed
up the perennial teaching

00:05:50.340 --> 00:05:54.390 align:middle line:84%
when he said, "The
end of all religions

00:05:54.390 --> 00:05:58.070 align:middle line:84%
is the realizing
of God in the soul.

00:05:58.070 --> 00:06:03.130 align:middle line:84%
That is the one
universal religion."

00:06:03.130 --> 00:06:06.640 align:middle line:84%
In this film, when we
use the word "God,"

00:06:06.640 --> 00:06:10.350 align:middle line:84%
it is simply a metaphor
for the transcendent,

00:06:10.350 --> 00:06:16.010 align:middle line:84%
pointing to the great mystery
beyond the limited egoic mind.

00:06:16.010 --> 00:06:19.640 align:middle line:84%
To realize one's true
self or immanent self

00:06:19.640 --> 00:06:23.510 align:middle line:84%
is to realize one's
divine nature.

00:06:23.510 --> 00:06:27.830 align:middle line:84%
Every soul has the potential
to manifest a new higher

00:06:27.830 --> 00:06:31.350 align:middle line:84%
level of consciousness,
to awaken

00:06:31.350 --> 00:06:34.695 align:middle line:84%
from its slumber and its
identification with form.

00:06:34.695 --> 00:07:05.080 align:middle line:90%


00:07:05.080 --> 00:07:08.110 align:middle line:10%
The writer and
visionary Aldous Huxley,

00:07:08.110 --> 00:07:10.990 align:middle line:10%
known for his book
"Brave New World,"

00:07:10.990 --> 00:07:13.960 align:middle line:10%
also wrote a book which
he entitled "The Perennial

00:07:13.960 --> 00:07:18.160 align:middle line:10%
Philosophy," in which he writes
about the one teaching that

00:07:18.160 --> 00:07:21.820 align:middle line:10%
comes back over and
over in history, taking

00:07:21.820 --> 00:07:26.020 align:middle line:10%
the form of the culture
in which it is realized.

00:07:26.020 --> 00:07:30.160 align:middle line:10%
He writes, "The Perennial
Philosophy is expressed most

00:07:30.160 --> 00:07:35.800 align:middle line:10%
succinctly in the Sanskrit
formula 'tat tvam asi'--

00:07:35.800 --> 00:07:41.440 align:middle line:10%
'that Thou art'-- the Atman,
or immanent eternal Self,

00:07:41.440 --> 00:07:45.730 align:middle line:10%
is one with Brahman, the
absolute principle of all

00:07:45.730 --> 00:07:51.280 align:middle line:10%
existence; and the last
end of every human being is

00:07:51.280 --> 00:07:55.000 align:middle line:10%
to discover the
fact for himself,

00:07:55.000 --> 00:07:58.135 align:middle line:10%
to find out who he
or she really is."

00:07:58.135 --> 00:08:03.876 align:middle line:90%


00:08:03.876 --> 00:08:07.360 align:middle line:84%
[MUSIC - DEVA PREMAL, "OM RAM
 RAMAYA"]

00:08:07.360 --> 00:08:11.290 align:middle line:84%
Each tradition is like a
facet of a jewel reflecting

00:08:11.290 --> 00:08:16.660 align:middle line:84%
a unique perspective of the same
truth while at the same time

00:08:16.660 --> 00:08:20.640 align:middle line:84%
echoing and
illuminating each other.

00:08:20.640 --> 00:08:24.780 align:middle line:84%
Whatever the language and
conceptual framework used,

00:08:24.780 --> 00:08:28.210 align:middle line:84%
all religions that reflect
the perennial teaching

00:08:28.210 --> 00:08:32.669 align:middle line:84%
have some notion that there is
a union with something greater,

00:08:32.669 --> 00:08:35.130 align:middle line:90%
something beyond us.

00:08:35.130 --> 00:08:38.595 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING SANSKRIT]

00:08:38.595 --> 00:09:09.850 align:middle line:90%


00:09:09.850 --> 00:09:14.080 align:middle line:84%
It is possible to learn from
and integrate the teachings

00:09:14.080 --> 00:09:18.910 align:middle line:84%
from one or many sources without
identifying a sense of self

00:09:18.910 --> 00:09:21.190 align:middle line:90%
with them.

00:09:21.190 --> 00:09:25.180 align:middle line:84%
It is said that all true
spiritual teachings are simply

00:09:25.180 --> 00:09:28.810 align:middle line:84%
fingers pointing to
the transcendent truth.

00:09:28.810 --> 00:09:33.380 align:middle line:84%
If we hold on to the dogma,
the teaching, for comfort,

00:09:33.380 --> 00:09:37.880 align:middle line:84%
we will be stunted in
our spiritual evolution.

00:09:37.880 --> 00:09:40.940 align:middle line:84%
To realize truth
beyond any concept

00:09:40.940 --> 00:09:46.190 align:middle line:84%
is letting go of all
clinging and attachment,

00:09:46.190 --> 00:09:48.470 align:middle line:84%
letting go of all
religious concepts.

00:09:48.470 --> 00:09:54.060 align:middle line:90%


00:09:54.060 --> 00:09:59.190 align:middle line:84%
From the ego's perspective, the
finger pointing you to Samadhi

00:09:59.190 --> 00:10:02.460 align:middle line:84%
is pointing straight
toward the abyss.

00:10:02.460 --> 00:10:06.150 align:middle line:90%


00:10:06.150 --> 00:10:09.020 align:middle line:84%
Saint John of the
Cross said, "If one

00:10:09.020 --> 00:10:12.350 align:middle line:84%
wishes to be sure of
the road they tread,

00:10:12.350 --> 00:10:15.800 align:middle line:84%
one must close their eyes
and walk in the dark."

00:10:15.800 --> 00:10:19.286 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING SANSKRIT]

00:10:19.286 --> 00:10:51.160 align:middle line:90%


00:10:51.160 --> 00:10:54.580 align:middle line:84%
Samadhi begins with a
leap into the unknown.

00:10:54.580 --> 00:10:58.052 align:middle line:90%
[THROAT SINGING]

00:10:58.052 --> 00:11:08.980 align:middle line:90%


00:11:08.980 --> 00:11:13.240 align:middle line:84%
In the ancient traditions,
in order to realize Samadhi,

00:11:13.240 --> 00:11:16.510 align:middle line:84%
it was said that one must
ultimately turn consciousness

00:11:16.510 --> 00:11:22.400 align:middle line:84%
away from all known objects,
from all external phenomena,

00:11:22.400 --> 00:11:25.180 align:middle line:84%
conditioned thoughts,
and sensations,

00:11:25.180 --> 00:11:30.850 align:middle line:84%
toward consciousness itself,
toward the inner source,

00:11:30.850 --> 00:11:33.055 align:middle line:84%
the heart, or essence,
of one's being.

00:11:33.055 --> 00:11:35.710 align:middle line:90%


00:11:35.710 --> 00:11:38.910 align:middle line:84%
In this film, when we
use the word "Samadhi,"

00:11:38.910 --> 00:11:41.710 align:middle line:84%
we are pointing to
the transcendent,

00:11:41.710 --> 00:11:44.200 align:middle line:84%
to the highest
Samadhi, which has

00:11:44.200 --> 00:11:47.580 align:middle line:90%
been named Nirvikalpa Samadhi.

00:11:47.580 --> 00:11:51.080 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SINGING]

00:11:51.080 --> 00:11:53.185 align:middle line:90%


00:11:53.185 --> 00:11:58.800 align:middle line:84%
In Nirvikalpa Samadhi, there is
a cessation of self activity,

00:11:58.800 --> 00:12:02.670 align:middle line:90%
of all seeking and doing.

00:12:02.670 --> 00:12:06.780 align:middle line:84%
We can only speak about what
falls away as we approach it

00:12:06.780 --> 00:12:11.610 align:middle line:84%
and what reappears
when we return from it.

00:12:11.610 --> 00:12:17.460 align:middle line:84%
There is neither perception nor
non-perception, neither thing

00:12:17.460 --> 00:12:20.880 align:middle line:84%
nor no thing,
neither consciousness

00:12:20.880 --> 00:12:24.000 align:middle line:90%
or unconsciousness.

00:12:24.000 --> 00:12:30.336 align:middle line:10%
It is absolute, unfathomable,
and inscrutable to the mind.

00:12:30.336 --> 00:12:33.528 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SINGING]

00:12:33.528 --> 00:12:34.900 align:middle line:90%


00:12:34.900 --> 00:12:36.960 align:middle line:84%
When the self
returns to activity,

00:12:36.960 --> 00:12:40.580 align:middle line:84%
there's a not knowing,
a kind of rebirth,

00:12:40.580 --> 00:12:43.520 align:middle line:84%
and everything
becomes new again.

00:12:43.520 --> 00:12:47.090 align:middle line:84%
We are left with the
perfume of the divine, which

00:12:47.090 --> 00:12:50.615 align:middle line:84%
lingers longer as one
evolves on the path.

00:12:50.615 --> 00:12:53.750 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SINGING]

00:12:53.750 --> 00:13:02.890 align:middle line:90%


00:13:02.890 --> 00:13:05.590 align:middle line:10%
There are numerous types
of Samadhi described

00:13:05.590 --> 00:13:08.900 align:middle line:10%
in the ancient traditions,
and language has created

00:13:08.900 --> 00:13:12.190 align:middle line:10%
much confusion over the years.

00:13:12.190 --> 00:13:14.590 align:middle line:10%
We are choosing to
use the word "Samadhi"

00:13:14.590 --> 00:13:17.410 align:middle line:10%
to point to the
transcendent union,

00:13:17.410 --> 00:13:20.410 align:middle line:10%
but we could have used a
word from another tradition

00:13:20.410 --> 00:13:22.900 align:middle line:10%
just as easily.

00:13:22.900 --> 00:13:26.980 align:middle line:84%
Samadhi is an ancient Sanskrit
term common to the Vedic,

00:13:26.980 --> 00:13:30.670 align:middle line:84%
Yogic, and Samkhya
traditions of India

00:13:30.670 --> 00:13:33.830 align:middle line:84%
and has permeated many
other spiritual traditions.

00:13:33.830 --> 00:13:36.460 align:middle line:90%


00:13:36.460 --> 00:13:42.090 align:middle line:84%
Samadhi is the eighth limb of
Patanjali's eight limbs of yoga

00:13:42.090 --> 00:13:44.985 align:middle line:84%
and the eighth part of the
Buddha's Noble Eightfold Path.

00:13:44.985 --> 00:13:48.130 align:middle line:90%


00:13:48.130 --> 00:13:51.280 align:middle line:84%
The Buddha used
the word "nirvana,"

00:13:51.280 --> 00:13:55.600 align:middle line:84%
the cessation of vana, or the
cessation of self activity.

00:13:55.600 --> 00:13:58.850 align:middle line:90%


00:13:58.850 --> 00:14:02.870 align:middle line:10%
Patanjali described
yoga, or Samadhi,

00:14:02.870 --> 00:14:07.370 align:middle line:10%
as "chitta vritti
nirodha," the Sanskrit

00:14:07.370 --> 00:14:14.780 align:middle line:10%
meaning "cessation of the
whirlpool, or spiral, of mind."

00:14:14.780 --> 00:14:18.190 align:middle line:84%
It is a disentangling
of consciousness

00:14:18.190 --> 00:14:23.074 align:middle line:84%
from the entire matrix,
or creatrix, of mind.

00:14:23.074 --> 00:14:26.518 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:14:26.518 --> 00:14:50.650 align:middle line:90%


00:14:50.650 --> 00:14:54.250 align:middle line:84%
Samadhi does not
signify any concept,

00:14:54.250 --> 00:14:57.400 align:middle line:84%
because to realize it
requires a dropping

00:14:57.400 --> 00:14:58.690 align:middle line:90%
of the conceptual mind.

00:14:58.690 --> 00:15:02.610 align:middle line:90%


00:15:02.610 --> 00:15:05.280 align:middle line:84%
Different religions
have used various words

00:15:05.280 --> 00:15:09.060 align:middle line:90%
to describe the divine union.

00:15:09.060 --> 00:15:14.900 align:middle line:84%
In fact, the word "religion"
itself means something similar.

00:15:14.900 --> 00:15:21.460 align:middle line:84%
In Latin, "religare" means
to rebind or reconnect.

00:15:21.460 --> 00:15:26.200 align:middle line:84%
It's a similar meaning to the
word yoga, which means to yoke,

00:15:26.200 --> 00:15:29.190 align:middle line:84%
to unite the worldly
with the transcendent.

00:15:29.190 --> 00:15:32.170 align:middle line:90%


00:15:32.170 --> 00:15:36.250 align:middle line:84%
In Islam, it is reflected in
the ancient Arabic meaning

00:15:36.250 --> 00:15:40.630 align:middle line:84%
of the word "Islam" itself,
which means submission

00:15:40.630 --> 00:15:43.660 align:middle line:90%
or supplication to God.

00:15:43.660 --> 00:15:47.290 align:middle line:84%
It signifies a total
humbling or surrender

00:15:47.290 --> 00:15:48.650 align:middle line:90%
of the self structure.

00:15:48.650 --> 00:15:53.180 align:middle line:90%


00:15:53.180 --> 00:15:59.070 align:middle line:10%
Christian mystics such as
Saint Francis of Assisi,

00:15:59.070 --> 00:16:06.450 align:middle line:10%
Saint Teresa of Ãvila, and
Saint John of the Cross describe

00:16:06.450 --> 00:16:12.930 align:middle line:10%
a divine union with God,
the kingdom of God within.

00:16:12.930 --> 00:16:17.720 align:middle line:84%
In the Gospel of Thomas,
Christ said, "The kingdom

00:16:17.720 --> 00:16:20.330 align:middle line:90%
is not here or there.

00:16:20.330 --> 00:16:22.520 align:middle line:84%
Rather, the kingdom
of the Father

00:16:22.520 --> 00:16:26.180 align:middle line:84%
is spread out upon the Earth,
and men do not see it."

00:16:26.180 --> 00:16:29.890 align:middle line:90%


00:16:29.890 --> 00:16:34.330 align:middle line:84%
The works of the Greek
philosophers Plato, Plotinus,

00:16:34.330 --> 00:16:38.260 align:middle line:84%
Parmenides, and
Heraclitus, when seen

00:16:38.260 --> 00:16:41.140 align:middle line:84%
through the lens of
the perennial teaching,

00:16:41.140 --> 00:16:42.695 align:middle line:90%
point towards the same wisdom.

00:16:42.695 --> 00:16:45.980 align:middle line:90%


00:16:45.980 --> 00:16:50.250 align:middle line:84%
Plotinus teaches that the
greatest human endeavor

00:16:50.250 --> 00:16:54.510 align:middle line:84%
is to guide the human soul
towards the supreme state

00:16:54.510 --> 00:16:57.690 align:middle line:84%
of perfection and
union with the One.

00:16:57.690 --> 00:17:03.490 align:middle line:90%


00:17:03.490 --> 00:17:06.740 align:middle line:10%
The Lakota medicine
and holy man Black Elk

00:17:06.740 --> 00:17:12.900 align:middle line:10%
said, "The first peace,
which is the most important,

00:17:12.900 --> 00:17:15.560 align:middle line:10%
is that which comes
within the souls of men

00:17:15.560 --> 00:17:19.190 align:middle line:10%
when they realize their
relationship, their oneness

00:17:19.190 --> 00:17:22.339 align:middle line:10%
with the universe
and all its powers,

00:17:22.339 --> 00:17:26.150 align:middle line:10%
and when they realize that
at the center of the universe

00:17:26.150 --> 00:17:30.230 align:middle line:10%
dwells Great Spirit and
that this center is really

00:17:30.230 --> 00:17:32.480 align:middle line:10%
everywhere.

00:17:32.480 --> 00:17:34.295 align:middle line:10%
It is within each of us."

00:17:34.295 --> 00:17:37.520 align:middle line:10%
[NON-ENGLISH SINGING]

00:17:37.520 --> 00:17:52.370 align:middle line:90%


00:17:52.370 --> 00:17:55.835 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:17:55.835 --> 00:17:59.820 align:middle line:90%


00:17:59.820 --> 00:18:04.260 align:middle line:84%
On the path to awakening,
unless we are in Samadhi,

00:18:04.260 --> 00:18:10.350 align:middle line:84%
there are always two polarities,
two doorways one can enter,

00:18:10.350 --> 00:18:12.040 align:middle line:90%
two dimensions--

00:18:12.040 --> 00:18:15.900 align:middle line:84%
one towards pure
consciousness, the other

00:18:15.900 --> 00:18:19.110 align:middle line:90%
towards the phenomenal world--

00:18:19.110 --> 00:18:22.230 align:middle line:84%
the upward current
toward the absolute

00:18:22.230 --> 00:18:25.290 align:middle line:84%
and the downward
current toward maya

00:18:25.290 --> 00:18:30.900 align:middle line:84%
and all that is manifested,
both seen and unseen.

00:18:30.900 --> 00:18:34.080 align:middle line:10%
The relationship between
relative and absolute

00:18:34.080 --> 00:18:36.270 align:middle line:10%
could be summed up in
the following quote

00:18:36.270 --> 00:18:40.440 align:middle line:10%
by Sri Nisargadatta Maharaj--

00:18:40.440 --> 00:18:43.890 align:middle line:10%
"Wisdom is knowing I am nothing.

00:18:43.890 --> 00:18:47.040 align:middle line:10%
Love is knowing I am everything.

00:18:47.040 --> 00:18:49.995 align:middle line:84%
And between the
two, my life moves."

00:18:49.995 --> 00:18:54.830 align:middle line:90%


00:18:54.830 --> 00:19:00.250 align:middle line:84%
What is born of this union is
a new divine consciousness.

00:19:00.250 --> 00:19:03.190 align:middle line:84%
Something is born out of
the marriage, or union,

00:19:03.190 --> 00:19:06.040 align:middle line:84%
of these polarities
or the collapse

00:19:06.040 --> 00:19:09.370 align:middle line:90%
of dualistic identification.

00:19:09.370 --> 00:19:14.050 align:middle line:84%
Yet, what is born is not a
thing, and it was never born.

00:19:14.050 --> 00:19:19.000 align:middle line:90%


00:19:19.000 --> 00:19:23.410 align:middle line:10%
Consciousness flowers,
creating something new,

00:19:23.410 --> 00:19:26.230 align:middle line:10%
creating what you could
call a perennial trinity.

00:19:26.230 --> 00:19:29.140 align:middle line:90%


00:19:29.140 --> 00:19:32.140 align:middle line:10%
God the Father,
the transcendent,

00:19:32.140 --> 00:19:35.230 align:middle line:10%
unknowable, and
changeless is united

00:19:35.230 --> 00:19:41.670 align:middle line:10%
with the Divine Feminine, which
is everything that changes.

00:19:41.670 --> 00:19:46.200 align:middle line:84%
This union brings about an
alchemical transformation,

00:19:46.200 --> 00:19:48.000 align:middle line:90%
a kind of death and birth.

00:19:48.000 --> 00:19:51.740 align:middle line:90%


00:19:51.740 --> 00:19:54.800 align:middle line:84%
In the Vedic teachings,
the divine union

00:19:54.800 --> 00:19:58.280 align:middle line:84%
is represented by two
fundamental forces--

00:19:58.280 --> 00:19:59.255 align:middle line:90%
Shiva and Shakti.

00:19:59.255 --> 00:20:02.350 align:middle line:90%


00:20:02.350 --> 00:20:05.620 align:middle line:10%
The names and faces
of the various gods

00:20:05.620 --> 00:20:09.490 align:middle line:10%
change throughout history, but
their fundamental attributes

00:20:09.490 --> 00:20:11.860 align:middle line:10%
remain.

00:20:11.860 --> 00:20:17.380 align:middle line:10%
What is born out of this union
is a new divine consciousness,

00:20:17.380 --> 00:20:22.890 align:middle line:10%
a new way of being in
the world, two polarities

00:20:22.890 --> 00:20:26.460 align:middle line:10%
inseparably one,
a universal energy

00:20:26.460 --> 00:20:30.900 align:middle line:10%
that is without center,
free of limitation.

00:20:30.900 --> 00:20:33.220 align:middle line:90%
It is pure love.

00:20:33.220 --> 00:20:35.970 align:middle line:84%
There is nothing to
be gained or lost,

00:20:35.970 --> 00:20:40.260 align:middle line:84%
because it is utterly
empty but absolutely full.

00:20:40.260 --> 00:20:48.116 align:middle line:90%


00:20:48.116 --> 00:20:51.560 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:20:51.560 --> 00:20:55.910 align:middle line:10%
Whether it is the mystery
schools of Mesopotamia,

00:20:55.910 --> 00:21:00.620 align:middle line:10%
the spiritual traditions of
the Babylonians and Assyrians,

00:21:00.620 --> 00:21:04.940 align:middle line:10%
religions of ancient Egypt,
Nubian and Kemetic cultures

00:21:04.940 --> 00:21:08.750 align:middle line:10%
of ancient Africa, the
shamanic and native traditions

00:21:08.750 --> 00:21:13.850 align:middle line:10%
around the world, the
mysticism of ancient Greece,

00:21:13.850 --> 00:21:23.750 align:middle line:10%
the Gnostics, the nondualists,
the Buddhists, the Taoists,

00:21:23.750 --> 00:21:33.230 align:middle line:10%
Jews, Zoroastrians, Jains,
Muslims, or Christians,

00:21:33.230 --> 00:21:35.690 align:middle line:10%
one finds that
their common link is

00:21:35.690 --> 00:21:39.560 align:middle line:10%
their highest spiritual insights
have allowed their adherence

00:21:39.560 --> 00:21:40.465 align:middle line:10%
to realize Samadhi.

00:21:40.465 --> 00:21:45.840 align:middle line:90%


00:21:45.840 --> 00:21:48.660 align:middle line:84%
The actual word
Samadhi means something

00:21:48.660 --> 00:21:55.190 align:middle line:84%
like to realize the sameness
or oneness in all things.

00:21:55.190 --> 00:21:58.050 align:middle line:90%
It means union.

00:21:58.050 --> 00:22:00.585 align:middle line:84%
It is uniting all
aspects of yourself.

00:22:00.585 --> 00:22:04.210 align:middle line:90%


00:22:04.210 --> 00:22:07.600 align:middle line:84%
But do not mistake
intellectual understanding

00:22:07.600 --> 00:22:12.110 align:middle line:84%
for the actual
realization of Samadhi.

00:22:12.110 --> 00:22:15.290 align:middle line:84%
It is your stillness,
your emptiness

00:22:15.290 --> 00:22:18.670 align:middle line:84%
that unites all levels
of the spiral of life.

00:22:18.670 --> 00:22:39.586 align:middle line:90%


00:22:39.586 --> 00:22:44.068 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:22:44.068 --> 00:22:55.520 align:middle line:90%


00:22:55.520 --> 00:22:58.590 align:middle line:10%
It is through the ancient
teaching of Samadhi

00:22:58.590 --> 00:23:01.120 align:middle line:10%
that humanity can
begin to understand

00:23:01.120 --> 00:23:03.780 align:middle line:10%
the common source
of all religions

00:23:03.780 --> 00:23:08.100 align:middle line:10%
and come into alignment once
again with the spiral of life,

00:23:08.100 --> 00:23:11.310 align:middle line:10%
Great Spirit,
Dhamma, or the Tao.

00:23:11.310 --> 00:23:14.200 align:middle line:90%


00:23:14.200 --> 00:23:18.040 align:middle line:84%
The spiral is the bridge that
extends from the microcosm

00:23:18.040 --> 00:23:19.180 align:middle line:90%
to the macrocosm.

00:23:19.180 --> 00:23:23.810 align:middle line:90%


00:23:23.810 --> 00:23:27.380 align:middle line:84%
From your DNA to the
inner Lotus of energy

00:23:27.380 --> 00:23:35.860 align:middle line:84%
that extends through the chakras
to the spiral arms of galaxies,

00:23:35.860 --> 00:23:40.230 align:middle line:84%
every level of soul is
expressed through the spiral

00:23:40.230 --> 00:23:47.720 align:middle line:84%
as ever-evolving branches,
living, exploring.

00:23:47.720 --> 00:23:50.840 align:middle line:84%
True Samadhi is
realizing the emptiness

00:23:50.840 --> 00:23:57.780 align:middle line:84%
of all levels of self,
all sheaths of the soul.

00:23:57.780 --> 00:24:01.560 align:middle line:84%
The spiral is the
endless play of duality

00:24:01.560 --> 00:24:03.830 align:middle line:90%
and the cycle of life and death.

00:24:03.830 --> 00:24:08.660 align:middle line:90%


00:24:08.660 --> 00:24:11.720 align:middle line:84%
At times, we forget our
connection to the source.

00:24:11.720 --> 00:24:20.760 align:middle line:90%


00:24:20.760 --> 00:24:25.570 align:middle line:84%
The lens we look
through is very small.

00:24:25.570 --> 00:24:29.170 align:middle line:84%
And we identify with being
a limited creature creeping

00:24:29.170 --> 00:24:33.490 align:middle line:84%
upon the Earth only to once
again complete the journey back

00:24:33.490 --> 00:24:40.520 align:middle line:84%
to the source, to the
center that is everywhere.

00:24:40.520 --> 00:24:48.460 align:middle line:90%


00:24:48.460 --> 00:24:53.150 align:middle line:84%
Chuang Tzu said, "When there
is no more separation between

00:24:53.150 --> 00:24:58.550 align:middle line:84%
'this' and 'that,' it is called
the still-point of the Tao.

00:24:58.550 --> 00:25:02.880 align:middle line:84%
At the still-point in
the center of the spiral,

00:25:02.880 --> 00:25:05.625 align:middle line:84%
one can see the
infinite in all things."

00:25:05.625 --> 00:25:14.090 align:middle line:90%


00:25:14.090 --> 00:25:18.740 align:middle line:84%
The ancient mantra
"om mani padme hum"

00:25:18.740 --> 00:25:21.580 align:middle line:90%
has a poetic meaning--

00:25:21.580 --> 00:25:27.690 align:middle line:84%
one awakens, or realizes,
the jewel within the Lotus.

00:25:27.690 --> 00:25:34.070 align:middle line:84%
Your true nature awakens within
the soul, within the world,

00:25:34.070 --> 00:25:34.905 align:middle line:90%
as the world.

00:25:34.905 --> 00:25:48.582 align:middle line:90%


00:25:48.582 --> 00:25:50.580 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:25:50.580 --> 00:25:54.750 align:middle line:84%
Using the hermetic principle
"as above, so below;

00:25:54.750 --> 00:25:58.590 align:middle line:84%
as below, so above,"
we can use analogies

00:25:58.590 --> 00:26:02.070 align:middle line:84%
to begin to understand the
relationship between mind

00:26:02.070 --> 00:26:05.690 align:middle line:84%
and stillness,
relative and absolute.

00:26:05.690 --> 00:26:13.090 align:middle line:90%


00:26:13.090 --> 00:26:16.820 align:middle line:84%
A way to begin to grasp
the non-conceptual nature

00:26:16.820 --> 00:26:21.351 align:middle line:84%
of Samadhi is to use the
analogy of the black hole.

00:26:21.351 --> 00:26:25.410 align:middle line:90%


00:26:25.410 --> 00:26:29.820 align:middle line:84%
A black hole is traditionally
described as a region of space

00:26:29.820 --> 00:26:33.330 align:middle line:84%
with a massive gravitational
field so powerful

00:26:33.330 --> 00:26:36.480 align:middle line:84%
that no light or
matter can escape.

00:26:36.480 --> 00:26:40.560 align:middle line:84%
New theories postulate that
all objects, from the tiniest

00:26:40.560 --> 00:26:44.730 align:middle line:84%
microscopic particles to
macrocosmic formations

00:26:44.730 --> 00:26:49.680 align:middle line:84%
like galaxies, have a black
hole or mysterious singularity

00:26:49.680 --> 00:26:52.440 align:middle line:90%
at their center.

00:26:52.440 --> 00:26:54.900 align:middle line:84%
In this analogy,
we're going to use

00:26:54.900 --> 00:26:57.480 align:middle line:84%
this new definition
of a black hole

00:26:57.480 --> 00:27:00.222 align:middle line:84%
as the center that
is everywhere.

00:27:00.222 --> 00:27:07.110 align:middle line:90%


00:27:07.110 --> 00:27:10.830 align:middle line:84%
In Zen, there are
many poems and koans

00:27:10.830 --> 00:27:15.990 align:middle line:84%
that bring us face to face
with the gateless gate.

00:27:15.990 --> 00:27:19.860 align:middle line:84%
One must pass the gateless
gate to realize Samadhi.

00:27:19.860 --> 00:27:24.460 align:middle line:90%


00:27:24.460 --> 00:27:29.440 align:middle line:84%
An event horizon is a boundary
in space-time beyond which

00:27:29.440 --> 00:27:32.590 align:middle line:84%
events cannot effect
an outside observer,

00:27:32.590 --> 00:27:36.430 align:middle line:84%
which means that whatever is
happening beyond the event

00:27:36.430 --> 00:27:40.690 align:middle line:90%
horizon is unknowable to you.

00:27:40.690 --> 00:27:44.440 align:middle line:84%
You could say that the event
horizon of a black hole

00:27:44.440 --> 00:27:48.360 align:middle line:84%
is analogous to
the gateless gate.

00:27:48.360 --> 00:27:53.710 align:middle line:84%
It is the threshold between
the self and no self.

00:27:53.710 --> 00:27:57.340 align:middle line:84%
There is no "me" that
passes the event horizon.

00:27:57.340 --> 00:28:01.460 align:middle line:90%


00:28:01.460 --> 00:28:06.470 align:middle line:84%
In the center of a black hole is
the one-dimensional singularity

00:28:06.470 --> 00:28:09.590 align:middle line:84%
containing the mass
of billions of suns

00:28:09.590 --> 00:28:15.710 align:middle line:84%
in an unimaginably small space,
effectively an infinite mass,

00:28:15.710 --> 00:28:19.550 align:middle line:84%
literally a universe in
something infinitesimally

00:28:19.550 --> 00:28:22.910 align:middle line:90%
smaller than a grain of sand.

00:28:22.910 --> 00:28:26.210 align:middle line:84%
The singularity is
something unfathomable,

00:28:26.210 --> 00:28:29.540 align:middle line:90%
beyond time and space.

00:28:29.540 --> 00:28:33.680 align:middle line:84%
According to physics,
movement is impossible.

00:28:33.680 --> 00:28:37.900 align:middle line:84%
The existence of
things is impossible.

00:28:37.900 --> 00:28:40.390 align:middle line:84%
Whatever it is,
it does not belong

00:28:40.390 --> 00:28:42.960 align:middle line:90%
to the world of perception.

00:28:42.960 --> 00:28:47.100 align:middle line:84%
Yet, it cannot be described
as merely stillness.

00:28:47.100 --> 00:28:49.095 align:middle line:84%
It is beyond stillness
and movement.

00:28:49.095 --> 00:28:51.750 align:middle line:90%


00:28:51.750 --> 00:28:56.430 align:middle line:84%
When you realize the center
that is everywhere and nowhere,

00:28:56.430 --> 00:28:59.700 align:middle line:90%
duality breaks down--

00:28:59.700 --> 00:29:02.915 align:middle line:84%
form and emptiness,
time and the timeless.

00:29:02.915 --> 00:29:06.650 align:middle line:90%


00:29:06.650 --> 00:29:09.800 align:middle line:84%
One could call it
a dynamic stillness

00:29:09.800 --> 00:29:13.940 align:middle line:84%
or a pregnant emptiness
within the center

00:29:13.940 --> 00:29:15.650 align:middle line:90%
of absolute darkness.

00:29:15.650 --> 00:29:18.600 align:middle line:90%


00:29:18.600 --> 00:29:25.080 align:middle line:84%
The Taoist teacher Lao Tzu
said, "Darkness within darkness.

00:29:25.080 --> 00:29:28.048 align:middle line:84%
The gateway to all
understanding."

00:29:28.048 --> 00:29:39.510 align:middle line:90%


00:29:39.510 --> 00:29:43.920 align:middle line:84%
The writer and comparative
mythologist Joseph Campbell

00:29:43.920 --> 00:29:47.580 align:middle line:84%
describes a recurring
symbol, part

00:29:47.580 --> 00:29:52.740 align:middle line:84%
of the perennial philosophy
which he calls the axis mundi,

00:29:52.740 --> 00:29:56.400 align:middle line:84%
the central point, or
the highest mountain,

00:29:56.400 --> 00:30:00.180 align:middle line:84%
the pole around
which all revolves,

00:30:00.180 --> 00:30:05.400 align:middle line:84%
the point where stillness
and movement are together.

00:30:05.400 --> 00:30:08.880 align:middle line:10%
From this center, a
mighty flowering tree

00:30:08.880 --> 00:30:15.712 align:middle line:10%
is realized, a Bodhi tree
that joins all worlds.

00:30:15.712 --> 00:30:19.170 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:30:19.170 --> 00:30:20.660 align:middle line:90%


00:30:20.660 --> 00:30:25.550 align:middle line:84%
Just as a sun gets sucked into
a black hole, when you approach

00:30:25.550 --> 00:30:31.040 align:middle line:84%
the Great Reality, your life
starts to revolve around it,

00:30:31.040 --> 00:30:33.553 align:middle line:90%
and you begin to disappear.

00:30:33.553 --> 00:30:36.864 align:middle line:90%
[THROAT SINGING]

00:30:36.864 --> 00:30:39.710 align:middle line:90%


00:30:39.710 --> 00:30:42.290 align:middle line:84%
As you approach
the immanent self,

00:30:42.290 --> 00:30:46.380 align:middle line:84%
it can be terrifying
to the ego structure.

00:30:46.380 --> 00:30:48.270 align:middle line:84%
The guardians of
the gate are there

00:30:48.270 --> 00:30:50.040 align:middle line:90%
to test those on their journey.

00:30:50.040 --> 00:30:54.120 align:middle line:90%


00:30:54.120 --> 00:30:58.470 align:middle line:10%
One must be willing to
face one's greatest fears

00:30:58.470 --> 00:31:02.730 align:middle line:10%
and at the same time
accept one's inherent power

00:31:02.730 --> 00:31:07.530 align:middle line:10%
to bring light to the
unconscious terrors

00:31:07.530 --> 00:31:09.360 align:middle line:10%
and the hidden beauty within.

00:31:09.360 --> 00:31:12.910 align:middle line:90%


00:31:12.910 --> 00:31:19.530 align:middle line:10%
If your mind is not moved,
if there is no self reacting,

00:31:19.530 --> 00:31:23.010 align:middle line:10%
then all phenomena
produced by the unconscious

00:31:23.010 --> 00:31:26.250 align:middle line:10%
arises and passes away.

00:31:26.250 --> 00:31:28.680 align:middle line:84%
This is the point in
the spiritual journey

00:31:28.680 --> 00:31:32.800 align:middle line:90%
where faith is most needed.

00:31:32.800 --> 00:31:34.235 align:middle line:90%
What do we mean by faith?

00:31:34.235 --> 00:31:36.910 align:middle line:90%


00:31:36.910 --> 00:31:40.140 align:middle line:90%
Faith is not the same as belief.

00:31:40.140 --> 00:31:44.040 align:middle line:84%
Belief is accepting something
on the level of mind

00:31:44.040 --> 00:31:47.730 align:middle line:90%
to bring comfort and assurance.

00:31:47.730 --> 00:31:51.150 align:middle line:84%
Belief is the mind's way
of labeling or controlling

00:31:51.150 --> 00:31:53.700 align:middle line:90%
experience.

00:31:53.700 --> 00:31:56.790 align:middle line:90%
Faith is actually the opposite.

00:31:56.790 --> 00:31:59.670 align:middle line:84%
Faith is staying in
the place of complete

00:31:59.670 --> 00:32:05.700 align:middle line:84%
not knowing, accepting whatever
arises from the unconscious.

00:32:05.700 --> 00:32:09.900 align:middle line:84%
Faith is surrendering to
the pull of the singularity,

00:32:09.900 --> 00:32:14.130 align:middle line:84%
to the dissolving, or
dismantling, of the self

00:32:14.130 --> 00:32:16.420 align:middle line:84%
in order to pass
the gateless gate.

00:32:16.420 --> 00:32:29.240 align:middle line:90%


00:32:29.240 --> 00:32:32.210 align:middle line:84%
The evolution and
structure of a galaxy

00:32:32.210 --> 00:32:36.290 align:middle line:84%
is closely tied to the
scale of its black hole,

00:32:36.290 --> 00:32:39.590 align:middle line:84%
just as your evolution
is tied to the presence

00:32:39.590 --> 00:32:43.600 align:middle line:84%
of the immanent self,
the singularity that

00:32:43.600 --> 00:32:44.575 align:middle line:90%
is your true nature.

00:32:44.575 --> 00:32:48.130 align:middle line:90%


00:32:48.130 --> 00:32:52.020 align:middle line:84%
We can't see the black hole,
but we can know about it

00:32:52.020 --> 00:32:55.540 align:middle line:84%
by the way things
move around it,

00:32:55.540 --> 00:32:59.710 align:middle line:84%
by how it interacts
with physical reality.

00:32:59.710 --> 00:33:04.510 align:middle line:84%
In the same way, we cannot
see our true nature.

00:33:04.510 --> 00:33:07.940 align:middle line:84%
The immanent self
is not a thing.

00:33:07.940 --> 00:33:12.010 align:middle line:84%
But we can observe
enlightened action.

00:33:12.010 --> 00:33:17.560 align:middle line:84%
As the Zen master Suzuki said,
"There are, strictly speaking,

00:33:17.560 --> 00:33:19.690 align:middle line:90%
no enlightened people.

00:33:19.690 --> 00:33:22.070 align:middle line:84%
There is only
enlightened activity."

00:33:22.070 --> 00:33:26.870 align:middle line:90%


00:33:26.870 --> 00:33:32.270 align:middle line:84%
We can't see it, just as
the eye cannot see itself.

00:33:32.270 --> 00:33:34.850 align:middle line:84%
We can't see it
because it is that

00:33:34.850 --> 00:33:38.440 align:middle line:90%
by which seeing is possible.

00:33:38.440 --> 00:33:42.620 align:middle line:84%
Like the black hole,
Samadhi is not nothingness,

00:33:42.620 --> 00:33:45.680 align:middle line:90%
and neither is it a thing.

00:33:45.680 --> 00:33:52.650 align:middle line:84%
It is the collapse of the
duality of thing and no thing.

00:33:52.650 --> 00:33:57.460 align:middle line:84%
There is no gate to
enter the Great Reality.

00:33:57.460 --> 00:34:00.740 align:middle line:90%
But there are infinite paths.

00:34:00.740 --> 00:34:05.470 align:middle line:10%
The paths, the dharmas,
are like an endless spiral

00:34:05.470 --> 00:34:08.830 align:middle line:10%
with no beginning and no end.

00:34:08.830 --> 00:34:11.860 align:middle line:84%
No one can pass
the gateless gate.

00:34:11.860 --> 00:34:18.370 align:middle line:84%
No one's mind has ever figured
out how, and none ever will.

00:34:18.370 --> 00:34:22.090 align:middle line:84%
No one can pass
the gateless gate.

00:34:22.090 --> 00:34:24.008 align:middle line:90%
So be no one.

00:34:24.008 --> 00:34:44.449 align:middle line:90%


00:34:44.449 --> 00:34:50.179 align:middle line:84%
Samadhi is the pathless
path, the golden key.

00:34:50.179 --> 00:34:54.300 align:middle line:84%
It is the end of our
identification with the self

00:34:54.300 --> 00:34:58.295 align:middle line:84%
structures that separate
our inner and outer worlds.

00:34:58.295 --> 00:35:13.035 align:middle line:90%


00:35:13.035 --> 00:35:15.510 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:35:15.510 --> 00:35:17.790 align:middle line:84%
There are many
developmental models

00:35:17.790 --> 00:35:23.160 align:middle line:84%
which describe the layers,
or levels, of self structure.

00:35:23.160 --> 00:35:28.130 align:middle line:84%
We will use an example
which is very ancient.

00:35:28.130 --> 00:35:33.530 align:middle line:84%
In the "Upanishads," the sheaths
which cover the atman, or soul,

00:35:33.530 --> 00:35:35.900 align:middle line:90%
are called koshas.

00:35:35.900 --> 00:35:42.200 align:middle line:84%
Each kosha is like a mirror,
a layer of the self structure,

00:35:42.200 --> 00:35:45.590 align:middle line:84%
a veil, or level, of
maya which distracts us

00:35:45.590 --> 00:35:52.100 align:middle line:84%
from realizing our true nature,
if we are identified with it.

00:35:52.100 --> 00:35:55.370 align:middle line:84%
Most people see the
reflections and believe

00:35:55.370 --> 00:35:56.930 align:middle line:90%
that that is who they are.

00:35:56.930 --> 00:35:59.520 align:middle line:90%


00:35:59.520 --> 00:36:05.850 align:middle line:84%
One mirror reflects the animal
layer, the physical body.

00:36:05.850 --> 00:36:08.450 align:middle line:84%
Another mirror
reflects your mind--

00:36:08.450 --> 00:36:13.610 align:middle line:84%
your thoughts, your
instincts and perceptions.

00:36:13.610 --> 00:36:16.340 align:middle line:84%
Another, your inner
energy, or prana,

00:36:16.340 --> 00:36:20.240 align:middle line:84%
which you can observe
when you turn inward.

00:36:20.240 --> 00:36:22.550 align:middle line:10%
Another mirror
reflects on the level

00:36:22.550 --> 00:36:27.890 align:middle line:10%
of the imaginal, which is the
higher mind, or wisdom, layer.

00:36:27.890 --> 00:36:31.250 align:middle line:10%
And there are layers of
transcendental, or nondual,

00:36:31.250 --> 00:36:34.780 align:middle line:10%
bliss that are experienced
as one approaches Samadhi.

00:36:34.780 --> 00:36:37.860 align:middle line:90%


00:36:37.860 --> 00:36:41.960 align:middle line:84%
There are potentially countless
mirrors, or aspects of self,

00:36:41.960 --> 00:36:45.750 align:middle line:84%
that one can differentiate, and
they are constantly changing.

00:36:45.750 --> 00:36:51.000 align:middle line:90%


00:36:51.000 --> 00:36:55.140 align:middle line:84%
Most people have yet to discover
the pranic, higher mind,

00:36:55.140 --> 00:36:58.050 align:middle line:90%
and nondual bliss layers.

00:36:58.050 --> 00:36:59.385 align:middle line:90%
They don't even know they exist.

00:36:59.385 --> 00:37:02.040 align:middle line:90%


00:37:02.040 --> 00:37:08.150 align:middle line:84%
These layers are informing your
life, but you do not see them.

00:37:08.150 --> 00:37:11.450 align:middle line:10%
The hidden mirrors
actually inform our lives

00:37:11.450 --> 00:37:14.770 align:middle line:10%
more than the ones
that are visible.

00:37:14.770 --> 00:37:17.330 align:middle line:84%
They are unseen,
because, for most people,

00:37:17.330 --> 00:37:20.240 align:middle line:84%
they are not fully
illuminated by consciousness.

00:37:20.240 --> 00:37:24.030 align:middle line:90%


00:37:24.030 --> 00:37:29.130 align:middle line:84%
Like Indra's net of jewels, the
mirrors all reflect each other,

00:37:29.130 --> 00:37:32.550 align:middle line:84%
and the reflections reflect
every other reflection

00:37:32.550 --> 00:37:34.900 align:middle line:90%
infinitely.

00:37:34.900 --> 00:37:38.310 align:middle line:84%
A change on one
level simultaneously

00:37:38.310 --> 00:37:39.555 align:middle line:90%
affects all levels.

00:37:39.555 --> 00:37:43.110 align:middle line:90%


00:37:43.110 --> 00:37:47.150 align:middle line:84%
Some of these mirrors may
be left in the shadows

00:37:47.150 --> 00:37:50.280 align:middle line:84%
unless we are fortunate enough
to have a competent guide

00:37:50.280 --> 00:37:53.490 align:middle line:84%
to help us shine
light upon them.

00:37:53.490 --> 00:37:58.830 align:middle line:84%
The truth is we don't
know what we don't know.

00:37:58.830 --> 00:38:02.646 align:middle line:84%
Now, imagine that you
shatter all the mirrors.

00:38:02.646 --> 00:38:04.470 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC CHANGES]

00:38:04.470 --> 00:38:09.560 align:middle line:84%
There's nothing reflecting
you back to yourself.

00:38:09.560 --> 00:38:10.490 align:middle line:90%
Where are you?

00:38:10.490 --> 00:38:14.590 align:middle line:90%


00:38:14.590 --> 00:38:18.985 align:middle line:84%
When the mind becomes still,
the mirrors cease to reflect.

00:38:18.985 --> 00:38:22.360 align:middle line:90%


00:38:22.360 --> 00:38:24.750 align:middle line:84%
There is no more
subject and object.

00:38:24.750 --> 00:38:29.000 align:middle line:90%


00:38:29.000 --> 00:38:31.790 align:middle line:84%
But do not mistake
the primordial state

00:38:31.790 --> 00:38:35.480 align:middle line:90%
for nothingness or oblivion.

00:38:35.480 --> 00:38:38.900 align:middle line:84%
The immanent self
is not something,

00:38:38.900 --> 00:38:40.320 align:middle line:90%
but neither is it nothing.

00:38:40.320 --> 00:38:48.550 align:middle line:90%


00:38:48.550 --> 00:38:51.550 align:middle line:90%
This source is not a thing.

00:38:51.550 --> 00:38:54.130 align:middle line:84%
It is emptiness, or
stillness, itself.

00:38:54.130 --> 00:38:57.670 align:middle line:90%


00:38:57.670 --> 00:39:02.890 align:middle line:84%
It is an emptiness that is
the source of all things.

00:39:02.890 --> 00:39:07.690 align:middle line:84%
Form is realized as
exactly emptiness.

00:39:07.690 --> 00:39:10.730 align:middle line:84%
Emptiness is realized
as exactly form.

00:39:10.730 --> 00:39:14.860 align:middle line:90%


00:39:14.860 --> 00:39:19.270 align:middle line:84%
This source is the
great womb of creation

00:39:19.270 --> 00:39:21.580 align:middle line:90%
pregnant with all possibilities.

00:39:21.580 --> 00:39:41.280 align:middle line:90%


00:39:41.280 --> 00:39:46.740 align:middle line:84%
Samadhi is the awakening of
impersonal consciousness.

00:39:46.740 --> 00:39:50.640 align:middle line:84%
Just as when you are having
a dream, upon awakening,

00:39:50.640 --> 00:39:53.400 align:middle line:84%
you realize that
everything in the dream

00:39:53.400 --> 00:39:56.130 align:middle line:90%
was just in your mind.

00:39:56.130 --> 00:39:58.740 align:middle line:84%
Upon realizing
Samadhi, it is realized

00:39:58.740 --> 00:40:02.760 align:middle line:84%
that everything in this world
is happening within levels

00:40:02.760 --> 00:40:07.150 align:middle line:84%
upon levels of energy
and consciousness.

00:40:07.150 --> 00:40:12.690 align:middle line:84%
It is all mirrors within
mirrors, dreams within dreams.

00:40:12.690 --> 00:40:17.610 align:middle line:84%
The you that you think
you are is both the dream

00:40:17.610 --> 00:40:18.450 align:middle line:90%
and the dreamer.

00:40:18.450 --> 00:40:34.180 align:middle line:90%


00:40:34.180 --> 00:40:39.500 align:middle line:84%
Whatever we say in
this film, let it go.

00:40:39.500 --> 00:40:43.080 align:middle line:90%
Don't capture it with the mind.

00:40:43.080 --> 00:40:47.040 align:middle line:10%
The soul is dreaming,
dreaming the dream of you.

00:40:47.040 --> 00:40:50.020 align:middle line:10%


00:40:50.020 --> 00:40:53.890 align:middle line:10%
The dream is everything
that is changing.

00:40:53.890 --> 00:40:57.630 align:middle line:10%
But it is possible to
realize the changeless.

00:40:57.630 --> 00:41:08.620 align:middle line:90%


00:41:08.620 --> 00:41:12.640 align:middle line:84%
This realization cannot be
understood with the limited

00:41:12.640 --> 00:41:13.920 align:middle line:90%
individual mind.

00:41:13.920 --> 00:41:22.740 align:middle line:90%


00:41:22.740 --> 00:41:26.310 align:middle line:84%
When we return from
Nirvikalpa Samadhi,

00:41:26.310 --> 00:41:29.770 align:middle line:84%
the mirrors begin
to reflect again,

00:41:29.770 --> 00:41:33.070 align:middle line:84%
and it is realized that
the world you now think you

00:41:33.070 --> 00:41:37.360 align:middle line:90%
are living in is actually you.

00:41:37.360 --> 00:41:43.030 align:middle line:84%
Not the limited you, which is
only a temporary reflection,

00:41:43.030 --> 00:41:46.540 align:middle line:84%
but you are aware
of your true nature

00:41:46.540 --> 00:41:51.480 align:middle line:90%
as the source of all that is.

00:41:51.480 --> 00:41:54.700 align:middle line:90%
This dawning of higher wisdom--

00:41:54.700 --> 00:41:59.140 align:middle line:90%
the embryo, prajna, or gnosis--

00:41:59.140 --> 00:42:03.400 align:middle line:90%
is what is born out of Samadhi.

00:42:03.400 --> 00:42:08.230 align:middle line:84%
According to the Book of
Job, Chokhma, or wisdom,

00:42:08.230 --> 00:42:11.270 align:middle line:90%
comes from nothingness.

00:42:11.270 --> 00:42:15.050 align:middle line:84%
This point of wisdom is
both infinitely small

00:42:15.050 --> 00:42:18.080 align:middle line:84%
and yet encompasses
the whole of being.

00:42:18.080 --> 00:42:21.590 align:middle line:84%
But it remains
incomprehensible until it

00:42:21.590 --> 00:42:27.410 align:middle line:84%
is given shape and form in the
palace of mirrors called Binah,

00:42:27.410 --> 00:42:31.550 align:middle line:84%
the womb carved out by higher
wisdom which gives shape

00:42:31.550 --> 00:42:33.125 align:middle line:90%
to the embryonic spirit of God.

00:42:33.125 --> 00:42:35.624 align:middle line:84%
[MUSIC - INDIAJIVA, "ABWOON
 D'BASHMAYA, THE LORD'S PRAYER"]

00:42:35.624 --> 00:42:39.150 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING ARAMAIC]

00:42:39.150 --> 00:43:02.080 align:middle line:90%


00:43:02.080 --> 00:43:05.545 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:43:05.545 --> 00:43:08.030 align:middle line:90%


00:43:08.030 --> 00:43:12.170 align:middle line:84%
The existence of the mirrors,
or the mind's existence,

00:43:12.170 --> 00:43:14.360 align:middle line:90%
is not a problem.

00:43:14.360 --> 00:43:20.690 align:middle line:84%
On the contrary, the error, or
aberration, of human perception

00:43:20.690 --> 00:43:26.350 align:middle line:84%
is that we identify
ourselves with it.

00:43:26.350 --> 00:43:32.080 align:middle line:84%
This illusion, that we are
the limited self, is maya.

00:43:32.080 --> 00:43:36.010 align:middle line:84%
The yogic teachings say
that to realize Samadhi,

00:43:36.010 --> 00:43:39.880 align:middle line:84%
one must observe the meditation
object until it disappears--

00:43:39.880 --> 00:43:42.930 align:middle line:90%


00:43:42.930 --> 00:43:49.290 align:middle line:84%
until you disappear
into it or it into you.

00:43:49.290 --> 00:43:51.990 align:middle line:84%
Although the language in
the various traditions

00:43:51.990 --> 00:43:55.590 align:middle line:84%
is dissimilar, at
their root, they all

00:43:55.590 --> 00:44:00.030 align:middle line:84%
point towards a cessation
of self-identification and

00:44:00.030 --> 00:44:03.180 align:middle line:90%
self-centered activity.

00:44:03.180 --> 00:44:06.720 align:middle line:84%
The Buddha always taught
in negative terms.

00:44:06.720 --> 00:44:09.000 align:middle line:84%
He taught to
investigate directly

00:44:09.000 --> 00:44:12.390 align:middle line:84%
into the working of
the self structure.

00:44:12.390 --> 00:44:16.110 align:middle line:84%
He didn't say what
Samadhi was except that it

00:44:16.110 --> 00:44:20.170 align:middle line:90%
was the end of suffering.

00:44:20.170 --> 00:44:24.920 align:middle line:10%
In Advaita Vedanta, there is
a term, "neti neti," which

00:44:24.920 --> 00:44:28.770 align:middle line:10%
means "not this, not that."

00:44:28.770 --> 00:44:31.740 align:middle line:84%
People on the path
to self-realization

00:44:31.740 --> 00:44:36.330 align:middle line:84%
inquire into their true nature,
or the nature of brahman,

00:44:36.330 --> 00:44:39.000 align:middle line:84%
by first discovering
what they are not.

00:44:39.000 --> 00:44:43.120 align:middle line:90%


00:44:43.120 --> 00:44:48.070 align:middle line:84%
Similarly, in Christianity,
Saint Teresa of Ãvila described

00:44:48.070 --> 00:44:51.820 align:middle line:84%
an approach to prayer
based on the negative path,

00:44:51.820 --> 00:44:58.060 align:middle line:84%
or via negativa, a prayer of
quiet, surrender, and union,

00:44:58.060 --> 00:45:00.970 align:middle line:84%
which is the only way to
approach the absolute.

00:45:00.970 --> 00:45:03.810 align:middle line:90%


00:45:03.810 --> 00:45:07.470 align:middle line:84%
Through this gradual
process of stripping away,

00:45:07.470 --> 00:45:10.920 align:middle line:84%
one drops anything
that is not permanent,

00:45:10.920 --> 00:45:14.870 align:middle line:90%
anything that is changing--

00:45:14.870 --> 00:45:19.830 align:middle line:84%
the mind, the ego construct,
and all phenomena,

00:45:19.830 --> 00:45:22.820 align:middle line:84%
including the hidden
layers of self.

00:45:22.820 --> 00:45:26.690 align:middle line:84%
The unconscious must
become transparent in order

00:45:26.690 --> 00:45:29.960 align:middle line:90%
to reflect the one source.

00:45:29.960 --> 00:45:33.395 align:middle line:84%
If there is some deep knowing
or some self operating

00:45:33.395 --> 00:45:36.650 align:middle line:84%
in the unconscious,
then our lives

00:45:36.650 --> 00:45:40.370 align:middle line:84%
remain locked into a
labyrinth of hidden patterns

00:45:40.370 --> 00:45:42.700 align:middle line:84%
that comprise the
undiscovered self.

00:45:42.700 --> 00:45:48.820 align:middle line:90%


00:45:48.820 --> 00:45:53.500 align:middle line:84%
When all layers of self
are revealed as empty,

00:45:53.500 --> 00:45:58.788 align:middle line:84%
then one becomes free from the
self, free from all concepts.

00:45:58.788 --> 00:46:02.134 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:46:02.134 --> 00:46:05.970 align:middle line:90%


00:46:05.970 --> 00:46:08.430 align:middle line:84%
A turning point
in your evolution

00:46:08.430 --> 00:46:11.540 align:middle line:84%
is when you realize you
don't know who you are.

00:46:11.540 --> 00:46:13.502 align:middle line:90%


00:46:13.502 --> 00:46:15.002 align:middle line:84%
[MUSIC - DANIEL
SCHMIDT, "GATE GATE,

00:46:15.002 --> 00:46:16.418 align:middle line:84%
THE HEART SUTRA
DEEP VOICE CHANT"]

00:46:16.418 --> 00:46:19.280 align:middle line:90%
Who experiences the breath?

00:46:19.280 --> 00:46:22.120 align:middle line:90%
Who experiences the taste?

00:46:22.120 --> 00:46:31.610 align:middle line:84%
Who experiences the chant,
the ritual, the dance,

00:46:31.610 --> 00:46:34.160 align:middle line:90%
the mountain?

00:46:34.160 --> 00:46:36.470 align:middle line:90%
Witness the witness.

00:46:36.470 --> 00:46:37.515 align:middle line:90%
Observe the observer.

00:46:37.515 --> 00:46:40.680 align:middle line:90%


00:46:40.680 --> 00:46:43.410 align:middle line:84%
At first, when you
observe the observer,

00:46:43.410 --> 00:46:46.960 align:middle line:84%
you will only see
the false self.

00:46:46.960 --> 00:46:50.390 align:middle line:84%
But if you are persistent,
it will give way.

00:46:50.390 --> 00:46:53.617 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING SANSKRIT]

00:46:53.617 --> 00:46:54.540 align:middle line:90%


00:46:54.540 --> 00:47:02.140 align:middle line:84%
Inquire directly into who or
what experiences unblinkingly,

00:47:02.140 --> 00:47:08.220 align:middle line:84%
piercingly, penetratingly, with
the full force of your being.

00:47:08.220 --> 00:47:11.184 align:middle line:90%


00:47:11.184 --> 00:47:14.642 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING SANSKRIT]

00:47:14.642 --> 00:47:40.824 align:middle line:90%


00:47:40.824 --> 00:47:44.282 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:47:44.282 --> 00:47:48.310 align:middle line:90%


00:47:48.310 --> 00:47:52.360 align:middle line:90%
There is no self that awakens.

00:47:52.360 --> 00:47:56.590 align:middle line:90%
There is no you that awakens.

00:47:56.590 --> 00:47:59.690 align:middle line:84%
What you are awakening
from is the illusion

00:47:59.690 --> 00:48:05.970 align:middle line:84%
of the separate self, from
the dream of a limited you.

00:48:05.970 --> 00:48:08.890 align:middle line:90%
To talk about it is meaningless.

00:48:08.890 --> 00:48:12.640 align:middle line:84%
There must be an actual
cessation of the self

00:48:12.640 --> 00:48:15.800 align:middle line:90%
to realize directly what it is.

00:48:15.800 --> 00:48:19.660 align:middle line:84%
And once it is realized,
there is nothing

00:48:19.660 --> 00:48:22.680 align:middle line:90%
that can be said about it.

00:48:22.680 --> 00:48:27.750 align:middle line:84%
As soon as you say something,
you are back in the mind.

00:48:27.750 --> 00:48:30.350 align:middle line:90%
I have already said too much.

00:48:30.350 --> 00:48:33.850 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:48:33.850 --> 00:48:40.350 align:middle line:90%


00:48:40.350 --> 00:48:44.280 align:middle line:84%
We normally have three
states of consciousness--

00:48:44.280 --> 00:48:48.170 align:middle line:84%
waking, dreaming,
and deep sleep.

00:48:48.170 --> 00:48:53.030 align:middle line:84%
Samadhi is sometimes referred to
as the fourth state, the ground

00:48:53.030 --> 00:48:58.130 align:middle line:84%
state of consciousness, a
primordial awakeness that

00:48:58.130 --> 00:49:02.090 align:middle line:84%
can become present
continuously and in parallel

00:49:02.090 --> 00:49:05.920 align:middle line:84%
with the other
consciousness states.

00:49:05.920 --> 00:49:08.330 align:middle line:84%
In Vedanta, this
is called turiya.

00:49:08.330 --> 00:49:11.900 align:middle line:90%


00:49:11.900 --> 00:49:15.920 align:middle line:84%
Other terms for turiya
are Christ consciousness,

00:49:15.920 --> 00:49:23.420 align:middle line:84%
Krishna consciousness, Buddha
nature, or Sahaja Samadhi.

00:49:23.420 --> 00:49:26.390 align:middle line:84%
In Sahaja Samadhi,
the immanent self

00:49:26.390 --> 00:49:29.560 align:middle line:84%
stays present along
with the full use

00:49:29.560 --> 00:49:32.780 align:middle line:90%
of all human functions.

00:49:32.780 --> 00:49:36.200 align:middle line:84%
The stillness is unmoving
at the center of the spiral

00:49:36.200 --> 00:49:39.340 align:middle line:90%
of changing phenomenon.

00:49:39.340 --> 00:49:44.260 align:middle line:84%
Thoughts, feelings, sensations,
and energy revolve around it

00:49:44.260 --> 00:49:46.610 align:middle line:90%
at the circumference.

00:49:46.610 --> 00:49:50.530 align:middle line:84%
But the degree of
stillness, or I am-ness,

00:49:50.530 --> 00:49:55.320 align:middle line:84%
remains during outer activity,
exactly as in meditation.

00:49:55.320 --> 00:49:58.150 align:middle line:90%


00:49:58.150 --> 00:50:02.350 align:middle line:84%
It is possible that the immanent
self will remain present,

00:50:02.350 --> 00:50:08.660 align:middle line:84%
even during deep sleep, that
your awareness of "I am"

00:50:08.660 --> 00:50:13.385 align:middle line:84%
does not come and go, even as
states of consciousness change.

00:50:13.385 --> 00:50:20.860 align:middle line:90%


00:50:20.860 --> 00:50:22.135 align:middle line:90%
This is yogic sleep.

00:50:22.135 --> 00:50:25.250 align:middle line:90%


00:50:25.250 --> 00:50:28.230 align:middle line:84%
In the Song of Songs,
or the Song of Solomon,

00:50:28.230 --> 00:50:32.910 align:middle line:84%
from the Hebrew Bible, or
Old Testament, it reads,

00:50:32.910 --> 00:50:37.400 align:middle line:90%
"I sleep, but my heart waketh."

00:50:37.400 --> 00:50:42.560 align:middle line:84%
This realization of the eternal
impersonal consciousness

00:50:42.560 --> 00:50:46.880 align:middle line:84%
is reflected in the words
of Christ when he said.

00:50:46.880 --> 00:50:50.270 align:middle line:90%
"Before Abraham was, I am."

00:50:50.270 --> 00:50:57.040 align:middle line:90%


00:50:57.040 --> 00:51:01.540 align:middle line:84%
One consciousness that shines
through countless faces,

00:51:01.540 --> 00:51:02.455 align:middle line:90%
countless forms.

00:51:02.455 --> 00:51:16.950 align:middle line:90%


00:51:16.950 --> 00:51:20.280 align:middle line:84%
At first, it's like a
fragile flame borne out

00:51:20.280 --> 00:51:23.120 align:middle line:90%
of the polarities within you--

00:51:23.120 --> 00:51:26.270 align:middle line:84%
masculine penetrating
consciousness

00:51:26.270 --> 00:51:30.770 align:middle line:84%
with a surrender, or
opening, of feminine energy.

00:51:30.770 --> 00:51:34.130 align:middle line:90%
It is delicate and easily lost.

00:51:34.130 --> 00:51:37.940 align:middle line:84%
And one must take great care
to protect it and keep it alive

00:51:37.940 --> 00:51:38.960 align:middle line:90%
until it is mature.

00:51:38.960 --> 00:51:44.330 align:middle line:90%


00:51:44.330 --> 00:51:49.190 align:middle line:84%
Samadhi is simultaneously a
timeless state of consciousness

00:51:49.190 --> 00:51:54.380 align:middle line:84%
and a stage in an unfolding
development process, something

00:51:54.380 --> 00:51:56.480 align:middle line:90%
organic and growing in time.

00:51:56.480 --> 00:52:05.560 align:middle line:90%


00:52:05.560 --> 00:52:11.830 align:middle line:84%
As one spends more and more
time in Samadhi, in the now,

00:52:11.830 --> 00:52:16.510 align:middle line:84%
in the timeless, one takes
more and more direction

00:52:16.510 --> 00:52:21.790 align:middle line:84%
from the heart,
the soul, or atman

00:52:21.790 --> 00:52:23.880 align:middle line:84%
and less from the
conditioned structure.

00:52:23.880 --> 00:52:29.650 align:middle line:90%


00:52:29.650 --> 00:52:33.470 align:middle line:84%
This is how one becomes
free of the lower mind, free

00:52:33.470 --> 00:52:34.940 align:middle line:90%
of pathological thinking.

00:52:34.940 --> 00:52:39.310 align:middle line:90%


00:52:39.310 --> 00:52:41.950 align:middle line:90%
The inner wiring changes.

00:52:41.950 --> 00:52:44.620 align:middle line:84%
Energy no longer
flows unconsciously

00:52:44.620 --> 00:52:48.990 align:middle line:84%
in the old conditioned
structures,

00:52:48.990 --> 00:52:52.970 align:middle line:84%
which is another way of saying
one is no longer identified

00:52:52.970 --> 00:52:56.225 align:middle line:84%
with the self structure,
with the outer world of form.

00:52:56.225 --> 00:53:11.370 align:middle line:90%


00:53:11.370 --> 00:53:15.570 align:middle line:84%
To realize Samadhi
requires an effort so great

00:53:15.570 --> 00:53:20.010 align:middle line:84%
that it becomes a total
surrender of one's self

00:53:20.010 --> 00:53:23.900 align:middle line:84%
and a surrender so
encompassing that it

00:53:23.900 --> 00:53:28.370 align:middle line:84%
is a complete effort of one's
being, all of one's energy.

00:53:28.370 --> 00:53:31.970 align:middle line:90%


00:53:31.970 --> 00:53:37.560 align:middle line:84%
It is a balance of effort
and surrender, yin and yang,

00:53:37.560 --> 00:53:39.320 align:middle line:90%
a sort of effortless effort.

00:53:39.320 --> 00:53:44.490 align:middle line:90%


00:53:44.490 --> 00:53:47.920 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:53:47.920 --> 00:53:54.510 align:middle line:84%
The Indian mystic and yogi
Paramahamsa Ramakrishna said,

00:53:54.510 --> 00:53:57.750 align:middle line:84%
"Do not seek illumination
unless you seek it

00:53:57.750 --> 00:54:02.560 align:middle line:84%
as one whose hair is
on fire seeks a pond."

00:54:02.560 --> 00:54:04.345 align:middle line:84%
You seek it with
your whole being.

00:54:04.345 --> 00:54:07.030 align:middle line:90%


00:54:07.030 --> 00:54:10.060 align:middle line:84%
During one's ego
transcending practice,

00:54:10.060 --> 00:54:14.350 align:middle line:84%
it takes great courage,
vigilance, and perseverance

00:54:14.350 --> 00:54:20.630 align:middle line:84%
to keep the embryo
alive, to not fall back

00:54:20.630 --> 00:54:23.630 align:middle line:90%
into the patterns of the world.

00:54:23.630 --> 00:54:27.410 align:middle line:84%
It takes a willingness to
go against the current,

00:54:27.410 --> 00:54:31.010 align:middle line:84%
against the inexorable
crush of the matrix

00:54:31.010 --> 00:54:34.850 align:middle line:84%
and the grinding
wheels of samsara.

00:54:34.850 --> 00:54:39.170 align:middle line:84%
Every breath, every
thought, every action

00:54:39.170 --> 00:54:42.890 align:middle line:84%
must be for
realizing the source.

00:54:42.890 --> 00:54:48.260 align:middle line:84%
Samadhi is not realized by
effort nor is it effortless.

00:54:48.260 --> 00:54:51.200 align:middle line:90%
Let go of effort and non-effort.

00:54:51.200 --> 00:54:56.300 align:middle line:84%
It's a duality that
only exists in the mind.

00:54:56.300 --> 00:54:58.880 align:middle line:84%
The actual
realization of Samadhi

00:54:58.880 --> 00:55:02.980 align:middle line:84%
is so simple, so
undifferentiated that it

00:55:02.980 --> 00:55:05.810 align:middle line:84%
is always misconstrued
through language,

00:55:05.810 --> 00:55:09.440 align:middle line:90%
which is inherently dualistic.

00:55:09.440 --> 00:55:12.500 align:middle line:84%
There is only one
primordial consciousness

00:55:12.500 --> 00:55:15.590 align:middle line:84%
that awakens as
the world, but it

00:55:15.590 --> 00:55:18.275 align:middle line:84%
has been obscured by
many layers of mind.

00:55:18.275 --> 00:55:20.780 align:middle line:90%


00:55:20.780 --> 00:55:25.310 align:middle line:84%
Like the sun hidden behind the
clouds, as each layer of mind

00:55:25.310 --> 00:55:28.730 align:middle line:84%
is dropped, one's
essence is revealed.

00:55:28.730 --> 00:55:33.640 align:middle line:90%


00:55:33.640 --> 00:55:35.890 align:middle line:84%
As each layer of
mind is dropped,

00:55:35.890 --> 00:55:39.160 align:middle line:84%
people call it a
different Samadhi.

00:55:39.160 --> 00:55:41.530 align:middle line:84%
They give names to
different experiences

00:55:41.530 --> 00:55:43.270 align:middle line:90%
or different types of phenomena.

00:55:43.270 --> 00:55:55.400 align:middle line:90%


00:55:55.400 --> 00:55:59.210 align:middle line:84%
But Samadhi is so simple that
when you are told what it is

00:55:59.210 --> 00:56:02.810 align:middle line:84%
and how to realize it, your
mind will always miss it.

00:56:02.810 --> 00:56:05.650 align:middle line:90%


00:56:05.650 --> 00:56:11.230 align:middle line:84%
Actually, Samadhi is
not simple or difficult.

00:56:11.230 --> 00:56:15.340 align:middle line:84%
It is only the mind
that makes it so.

00:56:15.340 --> 00:56:18.640 align:middle line:84%
When there is no mind,
there is no problem,

00:56:18.640 --> 00:56:24.820 align:middle line:84%
because the mind is what needs
to stop before it is realized.

00:56:24.820 --> 00:56:26.840 align:middle line:90%
It is not a happening at all.

00:56:26.840 --> 00:56:37.340 align:middle line:90%


00:56:37.340 --> 00:56:40.220 align:middle line:10%
The most concise
teaching of Samadhi

00:56:40.220 --> 00:56:43.610 align:middle line:10%
is perhaps found
in this phrase--

00:56:43.610 --> 00:56:47.305 align:middle line:10%
"Be still and know."

00:56:47.305 --> 00:56:50.756 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:56:50.756 --> 00:56:59.630 align:middle line:90%


00:56:59.630 --> 00:57:04.550 align:middle line:84%
How can we use words and
images to convey stillness?

00:57:04.550 --> 00:57:09.830 align:middle line:84%
How can we convey
silence by making noise?

00:57:09.830 --> 00:57:11.810 align:middle line:84%
Rather than talking
about Samadhi

00:57:11.810 --> 00:57:15.800 align:middle line:84%
as an intellectual
concept, this film

00:57:15.800 --> 00:57:22.490 align:middle line:84%
is a radical call to inaction,
a call to meditation,

00:57:22.490 --> 00:57:25.484 align:middle line:90%
inner silence, and inner prayer.

00:57:25.484 --> 00:57:27.654 align:middle line:90%
[THROAT SINGING]

00:57:27.654 --> 00:57:28.770 align:middle line:90%
A call to stop--

00:57:28.770 --> 00:57:32.193 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC STOPS]

00:57:32.193 --> 00:57:39.040 align:middle line:90%


00:57:39.040 --> 00:57:43.478 align:middle line:84%
--stop everything that is driven
by the pathological egoic mind.

00:57:43.478 --> 00:57:46.760 align:middle line:90%


00:57:46.760 --> 00:57:48.184 align:middle line:90%
Be still and know.

00:57:48.184 --> 00:57:55.300 align:middle line:90%


00:57:55.300 --> 00:58:00.500 align:middle line:84%
No one can tell you what will
emerge from the stillness.

00:58:00.500 --> 00:58:03.710 align:middle line:84%
It is a call to act from
the spiritual heart.

00:58:03.710 --> 00:58:11.932 align:middle line:90%


00:58:11.932 --> 00:58:15.411 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:58:15.411 --> 00:58:22.400 align:middle line:90%


00:58:22.400 --> 00:58:26.340 align:middle line:84%
It's like remembering
something ancient.

00:58:26.340 --> 00:58:31.050 align:middle line:84%
The soul wakes up
and remembers itself.

00:58:31.050 --> 00:58:33.830 align:middle line:84%
It has been a
sleeping passenger,

00:58:33.830 --> 00:58:38.100 align:middle line:84%
but now the emptiness
awakens and realizes itself

00:58:38.100 --> 00:58:39.100 align:middle line:90%
as all things.

00:58:39.100 --> 00:58:44.860 align:middle line:90%


00:58:44.860 --> 00:58:49.960 align:middle line:84%
You can't imagine what Samadhi
is with the limited egoic mind,

00:58:49.960 --> 00:58:54.970 align:middle line:84%
just as you can't describe to
a blind person what color is.

00:58:54.970 --> 00:58:56.890 align:middle line:90%
Your mind can't know.

00:58:56.890 --> 00:58:58.780 align:middle line:90%
It can't manufacture it.

00:58:58.780 --> 00:59:02.230 align:middle line:90%


00:59:02.230 --> 00:59:06.040 align:middle line:84%
To realize Samadhi is to
see in a different way--

00:59:06.040 --> 00:59:10.555 align:middle line:84%
not to see separate things,
but to recognize the seer.

00:59:10.555 --> 00:59:15.900 align:middle line:90%


00:59:15.900 --> 00:59:20.760 align:middle line:84%
Saint Francis of Assisi said,
"What you are looking for

00:59:20.760 --> 00:59:21.675 align:middle line:90%
is what is looking."

00:59:21.675 --> 00:59:24.390 align:middle line:90%


00:59:24.390 --> 00:59:28.890 align:middle line:84%
Once you have seen the
moon, you can recognize it

00:59:28.890 --> 00:59:32.790 align:middle line:90%
in every reflection.

00:59:32.790 --> 00:59:36.420 align:middle line:84%
The true self has
always been there.

00:59:36.420 --> 00:59:38.580 align:middle line:90%
It is in everything.

00:59:38.580 --> 00:59:40.800 align:middle line:84%
But you have not
realized its presence.

00:59:40.800 --> 00:59:43.920 align:middle line:90%


00:59:43.920 --> 00:59:49.140 align:middle line:84%
When you learn to recognize
and abide as the true self

00:59:49.140 --> 00:59:54.600 align:middle line:84%
beyond the mind and senses, it
is possible to experience awe

00:59:54.600 --> 00:59:55.710 align:middle line:90%
at the most mundane.

00:59:55.710 --> 00:59:58.560 align:middle line:90%


00:59:58.560 --> 00:59:59.795 align:middle line:90%
We become awe.

00:59:59.795 --> 01:00:09.190 align:middle line:90%


01:00:09.190 --> 01:00:12.400 align:middle line:84%
Do not try to be
free of desires,

01:00:12.400 --> 01:00:17.620 align:middle line:84%
because wanting to be free
of desires is a desire.

01:00:17.620 --> 01:00:21.490 align:middle line:84%
You can't try to be still,
because your very effort is

01:00:21.490 --> 01:00:22.290 align:middle line:90%
movement.

01:00:22.290 --> 01:00:26.450 align:middle line:90%


01:00:26.450 --> 01:00:30.395 align:middle line:84%
Realize the stillness that
is always already present.

01:00:30.395 --> 01:00:32.940 align:middle line:90%


01:00:32.940 --> 01:00:35.690 align:middle line:90%
Be the stillness and know.

01:00:35.690 --> 01:00:39.250 align:middle line:90%


01:00:39.250 --> 01:00:41.680 align:middle line:84%
When all preferences
are dropped,

01:00:41.680 --> 01:00:44.140 align:middle line:90%
the source will be revealed.

01:00:44.140 --> 01:00:47.620 align:middle line:84%
But do not cling
even to the source.

01:00:47.620 --> 01:00:53.080 align:middle line:84%
The Great Reality, Tao,
is not one, not two.

01:00:53.080 --> 01:00:55.750 align:middle line:90%


01:00:55.750 --> 01:01:00.850 align:middle line:84%
Ramana Maharshi said,
"The self is only one.

01:01:00.850 --> 01:01:04.780 align:middle line:90%
If it is limited, it is the ego.

01:01:04.780 --> 01:01:09.130 align:middle line:84%
If unlimited, it is infinite
and the Great Reality."

01:01:09.130 --> 01:01:15.930 align:middle line:90%


01:01:15.930 --> 01:01:20.900 align:middle line:10%
If you believe what is being
said, you've missed it.

01:01:20.900 --> 01:01:24.820 align:middle line:84%
If you disbelieve,
you've also missed it.

01:01:24.820 --> 01:01:29.350 align:middle line:84%
Belief and disbelief operate
on the level of mind.

01:01:29.350 --> 01:01:31.850 align:middle line:90%
They require a knowing.

01:01:31.850 --> 01:01:35.240 align:middle line:84%
But if you enter into
your own investigation,

01:01:35.240 --> 01:01:38.600 align:middle line:84%
examining all of the
aspects of your own being,

01:01:38.600 --> 01:01:41.810 align:middle line:84%
finding out who is
doing the investigating,

01:01:41.810 --> 01:01:44.540 align:middle line:84%
if you're willing to
live by the principle

01:01:44.540 --> 01:01:48.620 align:middle line:84%
"not my will but
higher will be done,"

01:01:48.620 --> 01:01:52.460 align:middle line:84%
if you're willing to
travel beyond all knowing,

01:01:52.460 --> 01:01:57.290 align:middle line:84%
then you may realize what I've
attempted to point towards.

01:01:57.290 --> 01:02:01.550 align:middle line:84%
Only then will you taste for
yourself the profound mystery

01:02:01.550 --> 01:02:03.515 align:middle line:90%
and beauty of simply existing.

01:02:03.515 --> 01:02:08.870 align:middle line:90%


01:02:08.870 --> 01:02:12.530 align:middle line:84%
There is another
possibility for life.

01:02:12.530 --> 01:02:16.670 align:middle line:84%
There is something
sacred, unfathomable

01:02:16.670 --> 01:02:21.230 align:middle line:84%
that can be discovered in the
still depths of your being,

01:02:21.230 --> 01:02:27.350 align:middle line:84%
beyond concepts, beyond dogmas,
beyond conditioned activity

01:02:27.350 --> 01:02:28.730 align:middle line:90%
and all preferences.

01:02:28.730 --> 01:02:33.380 align:middle line:90%


01:02:33.380 --> 01:02:37.070 align:middle line:84%
It is not acquired by
techniques, rituals,

01:02:37.070 --> 01:02:39.350 align:middle line:90%
or practices.

01:02:39.350 --> 01:02:42.240 align:middle line:90%
There is no "how" to get it.

01:02:42.240 --> 01:02:43.830 align:middle line:90%
There's no system.

01:02:43.830 --> 01:02:45.690 align:middle line:90%
There's no way to The Way.

01:02:45.690 --> 01:02:53.150 align:middle line:90%


01:02:53.150 --> 01:02:57.560 align:middle line:84%
As they say in Zen, it is
discovering your original face

01:02:57.560 --> 01:03:00.250 align:middle line:90%
before you were born.

01:03:00.250 --> 01:03:02.560 align:middle line:84%
It is not about adding
more to yourself.

01:03:02.560 --> 01:03:05.770 align:middle line:90%


01:03:05.770 --> 01:03:09.040 align:middle line:84%
It is becoming a
light unto oneself,

01:03:09.040 --> 01:03:12.350 align:middle line:84%
a light that dispels the
illusion of the self.

01:03:12.350 --> 01:03:17.060 align:middle line:90%


01:03:17.060 --> 01:03:21.080 align:middle line:84%
Life will always
remain unfulfilled

01:03:21.080 --> 01:03:24.800 align:middle line:84%
and the heart will
always remain restless

01:03:24.800 --> 01:03:31.034 align:middle line:84%
until it comes to rest in that
mystery beyond name and form.

01:03:31.034 --> 01:03:34.422 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:03:34.422 --> 01:03:53.991 align:middle line:90%


01:03:53.991 --> 01:03:56.784 align:middle line:84%
[MUSIC - DANIEL SCHMIDT
AND VICKI HANSEN,

01:03:56.784 --> 01:04:04.969 align:middle line:90%
"OM SHREEM LAKSHMI"]

01:04:04.969 --> 01:04:09.590 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING SANSKRIT]

01:04:09.590 --> 01:10:26.347 align:middle line:90%